ai.summary: A 9.6 km section of the Jubilee Greenway in the UK, rated moderate. This leg weaves through urban streets and green spaces, offering a varied route with city scenery and opportunities for parkland views.
ai.terrain_summary: Mixed surfaces including tarmac pavements, compact gravel paths, and park trails. Expect gentle gradients and occasional uneven sections in green spaces; some urban sections may have smoother surfaces.
ai.safety_notes: Plan for both urban and park environments: stay on marked paths, be aware of traffic at road crossings, and watch for pedestrians on shared routes. Check the weather forecast, carry water, wear sturdy footwear, and bring a navigation aid or map. Carry a small first-aid kit and phone with emergency contacts.
ai.best_seasons: Spring through Autumn (roughly March–October) offer the best conditions; winter hiking is possible with proper clothing and gear.
